Cinnamom Red Hot Ice Cream
  --All Recipes
  
2 c heavy whipping cream, divided
2 egg yolks 
2 c half-and-half
1 c cinnamon red hot candies

Whisk 1 c cream and egg yolks together in a bowl until smooth. Combine half-and-half, 1 c cream, and red hot candies in a large saucepan over medium-low; cook, stirring with a wooden spoon, until candies dissolve, 5-10 min. Pour 1 c red hot candies mixture into the cream-egg mixture; whisk until mixture is evenly combined. Pour cream-egg mixture into red hot candies mixture in the saucepan. Cook and stir until a film forms on the back of a spoon when dipped into the mixture, keeping just under a boil, ~5 min. Pour red hot candies mixture through a sieve into a bowl to collect any undissolved candies. Cover the bowl with a clean towel and cool to room temperature. Refrigerate until chilled, ~1 hr. Pour red hot candies mixture into an ice cream maker and process according to manufacturers' instructions.


